CI for $\mu_d$ (or $\delta$): [*How was* $t^*$ calculated?]{style="color:#BF396F"}





::::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}
\begin{align}
\bar{x}_d &\pm t^*\cdot\frac{s_d}{\sqrt{n}}\\
-21.767 &\pm 2.018\cdot\frac{13.89}{\sqrt{43}}\\
-21.767 &\pm 2.018\cdot 2.118\\
-21.767 &\pm 4.275\\
(-26.042&, -17.493)
\end{align}
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}
Conclusion:\
We are 95% that the (population) mean difference in cholesterol levels after a vegetarian diet is between -26.042 mg/dL and -17.493 mg/dL.

-   [*Based on the CI, is there evidence the diet made a difference in cholesterol levels? Why or why not?*]{style="color:#BF396F"}
:::
