::: {.column width="50%"}
[What changes in each of the steps?]{style="color:#BF396F"}

1.  Set the [**level of significance**]{style="color:#BF396F"} $\alpha$

2.  Specify the [**hypotheses**]{style="color:#BF396F"} $H_0$ and $H_A$

    -   Alternative: one- or two-sided?

3.  Calculate the [**test statistic**]{style="color:#BF396F"}.

4.  Calculate the [**p-value**]{style="color:#BF396F"} based on the observed test statistic and its sampling distribution

5.  Write a [**conclusion**]{style="color:#BF396F"} to the hypothesis test
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}
